    "title": "Revision & Feedback Process SOP",
    "date": "2026-07-07",
    "content": "\n\n## 🔄 Revision & Feedback Process SOP\n\n## Owner: Delivery Lead\n\n## Trigger: Client submits a revision request\n\nKey tools used in this SOP:\n\n💬 ClickUp — Client Feedback & Revisions list, task comments, Feedback Form (Business plan)\n\n## Revital Hub — Content Strategy Builder\n\n✅ QC Checklist doc — must be re-run after every revision before returning to client\n\n📞 Client Communication Policy — Part B for portal redirect scripts and escalation\n\n## Steps\n\n## 1. Receive the Revision\n\n- 💬 All revision requests must be submitted through the Client Feedback & Revisions list in ClickUp — either via the Submit Feedback or a Revision Request form (once Business plan is active — see Section\n\n## A below) or by creating a task directly\n\n- If a client submits revisions via email or text, use the approved script from Client Communication\nPolicy Part B to redirect them to the portal, then log the revision in ClickUp\n\n- Never action a revision that was not submitted through the portal — this breaks the tracking system\n\n## 2. Log the Revision\n\n- 💬 Create or update the task in Client Feedback & Revisions\n- Tag the related deliverable task\n- Update the Revision Round number on the deliverable task\n- Set priority: Urgent / High / Normal / Low\n\n## 3. Scope Check\n\n- Check if the revision is within the contracted scope\n\n- 📋 Reference the client's Scope of Work Log in ClickUp Legal folder\n- If it exceeds the agreed revision rounds or changes scope significantly, flag to the account manager before proceeding — a Change Order is required; reference the Change Order Process SOP in the\n\n- Reference the client's Content Strategy Builder profile to ensure revised content still aligns with the approved strategy\n- Complete the revision and move back to Internal Review\n\n- ✅ Re-run QC — open the QC Checklist doc and run the Universal Checklist plus the relevant service- ✅ specific section\n- Log QC completion comment on the task before moving to Client Review\n- Notify the client the revised version is ready — remind them of the 48-hour approval window per the\n\n## Client Communication Policy\n\n## 5. Final Approval\n\n- Once approved, move to Approved → Published\n- Log completion in the Comments field of the original deliverable task\n\nMaximum revision rounds are defined in the client's contract. Any request beyond the agreed rounds requires a signed Change Order before work begins.\n\nEvery revised version must pass QC before being sent to the client — no exceptions.\n\n## SECTION A — CLIENT FEEDBACK FORM SPEC\n\n## Build this once ClickUp Business plan is active\n\nWhy this matters: A guided form structurally prevents vague feedback (\"I don't like it\") by requiring specific details upfront, and auto-creates a properly formatted task with all fields populated — eliminating manual data entry and inconsistent revision requests.\n\n## Form Name: Submit Feedback or a Revision Request\n\nWhere to Build It: 💬 Client Feedback & Revisions list → Views → + Add View → Form\n\n## Form Fields\n\n## Field 1 — Your Name\n\n## Type: Short Text\n\n## Required: Yes\n\nHelper text: Enter the name of the content or campaign exactly as it appeared in your Client Review email\n\nPlaceholder: e.g. May Week 2 — Instagram Reel — Mother's Day\n\n## Field 3 — Service\n\n## Type: Dropdown — Single Select\n\n## ✅ Required: Yes\n\n## Options: (reuse existing Service(s) field options)\n\n## Organic Social\n\n## Paid Social\n\n## Paid Search\n\nSEO\n\n## Email Marketing\n\n## Website Design\n\n## Inbound Marketing\n\n## Strategy\n\nField 4 — What needs to change?\n\n## Type: Long Text\n\n## ✅ Required: Yes\n\nHelper text: Be as specific as possible — this helps us get it right on the first try\n\nPlaceholder:\n\nExample: \"Can we change the font color to our brand blue (#1A73E8)?\"\n\nExample: \"The headline feels too formal — try something like 'Ready to grow your brand?'\"\n\nExample: \"At 0:23 the text is too small on mobile — increase the font size\"\n\nTry to avoid: \"I don't like it\" or \"change the copy\" — the more specific, the faster we can act\n\n## Field 5 — Reference Image or Example (optional)\n\n## Type: File Upload\n\n## ❌ Required: No\n\nHelper text: Got an example of what you're looking for? Attach it here — a picture is worth a thousand words\n\n## Urgent — needed within 24 hours\n\n## High — needed within 2 business days\n\n## Normal — standard revision timeline\n\n## Low — no rush\n\nMaps directly to the task Priority field — Urgent/High/Normal/Low.\n\nField 7 — Anything else we should know?\n\n## Type: Long Text\n\n## ❌ Required: No\n\n## Placeholder: Any additional context, deadlines, or notes\n\n## Form Settings\n\n## Setting Value\n\n✅ 💬\n\n## Auto-create task Yes — task created in\n\n## Client Feedback & Revisions\n\n## Default Status on creation Brief Received (acts as\n\n## \"Feedback Received\" stage)\n\nMap Priority field From Field 6 — How urgent is this?\n\n## Map Service(s) field From Field 3 — Service\n\n## Notify on submission Account Manager — instant notification\n\n## Thank You Message\n\nGot it — thank you!\n\nYour feedback has been received and logged. Your account manager will review it and follow up within 1 business day. You can track the status of this request anytime in your portal under Feedback & Revisions.\n\n| Setting | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Auto-create task | ✅ 💬 Yes — task created in Client Feedback & Revisions |\n| Default Status on creation | Brief Received (acts as \"Feedback Received\" stage) |\n| Map Priority field | From Field 6 — How urgent is this? |\n| Map Service(s) field | From Field 3 — Service |\n| Notify on submission | Account Manager — instant notification |\n\nDescription:\n\n## Submitted By: [Field 1]\n\n## Deliverable: [Field 2]\n\n## Feedback: [Field 4]\n\n## Reference Attached: [Field 5 if provided]\n\n## Urgency: [Field 6]\n\n## Additional Notes: [Field 7]\n\n## Once Built — Update These\n\n## Document What to Change\n\n## Client Portal Doc Replace \"Submit a Revision\n\nRequest\" button URL with the Form share link instead of the raw list link\n\n## ✍ Content Approval Already references this form\n\nWorkflow in Section 1 — confirm the link is added once built\n\n## 📋 Custom Field Options Add a note under Section 13\n\n## Reference documenting the form field mapping\n\nLast updated: June 2026 | Owner: Revital Productions Delivery Lead\n\n| Document | What to Change |\n|---|---|\n| Client Portal Doc | Replace \"Submit a Revision Request\" button URL with the Form share link instead of the raw list link |\n| ✍ Content Approval Workflow | Already references this form in Section 1 — confirm the link is added once built |\n| 📋 Custom Field Options Reference | Add a note under Section 13 documenting the form field mapping |\n\n"
