    "id": "sop-new-client-account-access-sop",
    "category": "Security & Access",
    "title": "New Client Account Access SOP",
    "date": "2026-07-19",
    "content": "\n\n## 🔐 New Client Account Access SOP\n\n## Owner: Delivery Lead\n\n## Trigger: New client onboarding — after kick-off call\n\nReference: Pull Section 8, 8B, and 8C of the client's completed intake form before beginning\n\nKey tools used in this SOP:\n\n🔐 📣\n\nRevital Hub — Access & Login Log and Client Ad Account Log (hub.revitalproductions.com → Account Management) — the source of truth for every platform access entry and ad account record\n\n📞 Client Communication Policy — channel guide for how to request access from clients\n\n## Pre-Access Review\n\nBefore requesting any access, review the following from the client's completed intake form:\n\n- Section 8, Q13 — Does the client have admin access to grant us?\n- If No or Not Sure → contact the client before proceeding — use the correct channel per the Client\n\n## Communication Policy (email for standard, phone if urgent)\n\n- Section 8, Q14 — Does a previous agency or developer hold access?\n- If Yes → review Section 8B for platform details and recovery status before requesting access\n\n- 🔐 Flag these platforms in the Hub's Access & Login Log (Access Restrictions field) with \"Recovery Needed\" and resolve before work begins\n- Section 8C, Q1 — How does the client prefer to share credentials?\n- Always follow their stated preference — never ask them to share passwords via email or ClickUp\n\n## Access Request Checklist\n\n## Platform Access Type Who Requests Timeline Intake Form Ref\n\n| Platform | Access Type | Who Requests | Timeline | Intake Form Ref |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n\n## Google Search Full User SEO Lead Day 1 Section 8, Q4\n\n## Console\n\n## Google Tag Admin or User Delivery Lead Day 1 Section 8, Q4\n\n## Manager\n\n## Google Business Manager SEO Lead Day 1 Section 8, Q4\n\n## Profile\n\nInstagram / Editor or Admin Content Lead Day 2 Section 8, Q2\n\n## Facebook Page\n\nTikTok Business Member Access Content Lead Day 2 Section 8, Q2\n\n## Account\n\nLinkedIn Company Content Admin Content Lead Day 2 Section 8, Q2\n\n## Page\n\nYouTube Channel Manager or Editor Content Lead Day 2 Section 8, Q2\n\nWebsite / CMS Editor or Developer Web Lead Day 3 Section 8, Q5\n\n## Access\n\nDomain / Hosting Collaborator or DNS Web Lead Day 3 Section 8, Q7\n\n## Access\n\nEmail Marketing Campaign Access Email Lead Day 3 Section 8, Q8\n\n## Platform\n\n## CRM Admin Access Account Manager Day 3 Section 8, Q10\n\nCanva / Design Editor or Admin Content Lead Day 3 Section 8, Q12\n\n## Tools\n\n## Revital Hub Client Profile Account Manager Day 1 N/A\n\n## Created\n\n## Logging Access\n\nFor every platform access received:\n\n🔐 1. Open the Access & Login Log in the Revital Hub\n\n| Google Search Console | Full User | SEO Lead | Day 1 | Section 8, Q4 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Google Tag Manager | Admin or User | Delivery Lead | Day 1 | Section 8, Q4 |\n| Google Business Profile | Manager | SEO Lead | Day 1 | Section 8, Q4 |\n| Instagram / Facebook Page | Editor or Admin | Content Lead | Day 2 | Section 8, Q2 |\n| TikTok Business Account | Member Access | Content Lead | Day 2 | Section 8, Q2 |\n| LinkedIn Company Page | Content Admin | Content Lead | Day 2 | Section 8, Q2 |\n| YouTube Channel | Manager or Editor | Content Lead | Day 2 | Section 8, Q2 |\n| Website / CMS | Editor or Developer Access | Web Lead | Day 3 | Section 8, Q5 |\n| Domain / Hosting | Collaborator or DNS Access | Web Lead | Day 3 | Section 8, Q7 |\n| Email Marketing Platform | Campaign Access | Email Lead | Day 3 | Section 8, Q8 |\n| CRM | Admin Access | Account Manager | Day 3 | Section 8, Q10 |\n| Canva / Design Tools | Editor or Admin | Content Lead | Day 3 | Section 8, Q12 |\n| Revital Hub | Client Profile Created | Account Manager | Day 1 | N/A |\n\n🔒 Never log actual passwords anywhere, including the Hub. Log the password manager location only (e.g. \"LastPass vault —\n\nAcme Wellness — Meta Business Manager\").\n\n## If Access Is Not Received in 5 Business Days\n\n- Follow up with the client using the correct channel per the Client Communication Policy — email for standard follow-up, phone if the delay is impacting the production timeline\n\n- 🔐 Log the follow-up date in the Hub's Access & Login Log Notes field\n- If still not received after 10 business days, escalate to the account manager — do NOT begin platform work without confirmed access\n- Adjust the production timeline if access delays push back the start of work — notify the client proactively per the communication policy\n\n## Access Recovery Protocol (Section 8B clients)\n\nIf the client's intake form Section 8B indicates a previous agency or developer holds access:\n\n1. Identify all platforms needing recovery using Section 8B, Q4 of the intake form\n\n🔐 2. Flag each platform in the Hub's Access & Login Log with \"Recovery Needed — [who controls it]\" in Access Restrictions\n\n3. Contact the previous agency or developer on the client's behalf if the client has given permission\n\n4. Guide the client through the platform's official access recovery process (Meta Business Help Center, Google\n\n## Ads account recovery, etc.)\n\n5. Do not begin work on any platform until access is fully recovered and confirmed\n\n🔐 6. Update the Hub's Access & Login Log once recovery is complete — clear the \"Recovery Needed\" flag and set Date Granted\n\nLast updated: June 2026 | Owner: Revital Productions Delivery Lead\n\n"
