    "date": "2026-07-19",
    "content": "\n\n## 🚪 Client Offboarding SOP\n\n## Owner: Account Manager\n\n## Trigger: Client gives notice or contract end date arrives\n\nKey tools used in this SOP:\n\n## 🔐 📣 🔗\n\nClickUp — CRM Deal record, client delivery folder,\n\n## Master Shared Links Tracker\n\n## Revital Hub — final audit run, client profile, Access & Login Log, Client Ad Account Log\n\n✅ QC Checklist — Section 1 + Section 10 on final report before delivery\n\n## 📧 Email Templates — Template #16 Offboarding Final Email\n\n📞 Client Communication Policy — Part B tone guidance for offboarding communication\n\n⚖ Contract Templates — Early Termination Agreement if applicable\n\n## Steps\n\n## 1. Confirm the Offboarding\n\n- Update Deal Onboarding Status to Offboarding in CRM\n- Confirm the last day of service in writing with the client — email confirmation required, not verbal only\n- Review the contract for any offboarding obligations (notice period, deliverables owed, access handoff timeline)\n- If the client is leaving before the contract end date, initiate the Early Termination Agreement from\n\n## ⚖ the Contract Templates doc\n\n## 2. Final Hub Audit Run\n\n- Log in to the Hub at hub.revitalproductions.com using your @revitalproductions.com email\n- Open the client's profile and run a final version of all applicable audits — Social Media Audit, SEO\n\n## Audit, UX/UI Audit\n\n- Screenshot or export the final audit scores — these go in the offboarding report as proof of improvement\n\n- Cancel any deliverables that cannot be completed in time — notify the client in writing\n- Do not start any new work after the offboarding date is confirmed\n- Deliver all final completed assets to the client\n\n## 4. Hand Off Access\n\n🔐 📣\n\n- Pull the client's entries from the Hub's Access & Login Log and Client Ad Account Log — use these as the complete list of platforms to hand back\n- Transfer ownership of ad accounts, social pages, and tools back to the client on all platforms\n- Remove all Revital Productions team member access from every client platform\n- Provide the client with any logins, credentials, or assets that belong to them\n- Remove the client's profile from the Revital Hub\n\n- 🔐 Log all access removals in the Hub's Access & Login Log by setting the Date Removed field\n\n## 5. Final Reporting\n\n- Build the final performance report using the Hub Monthly Report Template\n\n- ✅ Run Section 1 (Universal QC) and Section 10 (Monthly Report QC) from the QC Checklist before delivery\n- Include Hub audit scores from onboarding vs. offboarding to show improvement over the full engagement\n- Include key wins, results achieved vs. original objectives from Section 6 of the client's intake form\n- Include recommendations for what the client should focus on next\n\n- 📊 Upload to Reports & Analytics in the client's ClickUp portal\n\n## 6. CRM & Workspace Cleanup\n\n- Move Deal to Closed Won (positive exit) or Inactive (any other exit)\n- Log the Inactive Reason — reference the dropdown options in the CRM Guidelines doc\n- Update Client Health to the final rating\n- Archive the client's delivery folder in ClickUp\n- Update all custom fields — confirm End Date, Closed Date, and Billing are all accurate\n\n- 🔗 Archive the client's tracker tasks in the Master Shared Links Tracker: i. Open Master Shared Links Tracker → filter by the client's tag ii. Select all 7 tracker tasks for this client\n\niii. Click Delete — confirm deletion iv. This keeps the workspace tag list clean as you grow\n\n## 7. Relationship Maintenance\n\n- Send Email Template #16 — Offboarding Final Email — review Client Communication Policy Part\n\n## B for the correct tone\n\n- Ask for a Google or LinkedIn review within 7 days of offboarding — include the direct review link\n\n- ⭐ Log the review request in Testimonials & Reviews in the Internal Marketing folder in ClickUp\n- Tag the client's Deal record for a 90-day follow-up check-in in case of re-engagement\n\n## ✅ Offboarding Checklist\n\n## Offboarding confirmed in writing with client\n\n## Deal Onboarding Status updated to Offboarding in CRM\n\n## Early Termination Agreement issued if applicable\n\n## Final Hub audits run and scores exported\n\nAll in-flight deliverables completed or cancelled — client notified\n\n## All remaining deliverables passed QC before delivery\n\n## All platform access transferred back to client\n\n## All Revital team access removed from client platforms\n\n## 🔐 All access removals logged in the Hub's Access & Login Log\n\n## Client Hub profile removed\n\n## Final performance report built, QC passed, and delivered\n\n## Report uploaded to client portal\n\n## Deal moved to Closed Won or Inactive in CRM\n\n## Inactive Reason logged\n\n## Client delivery folder archived in ClickUp\n\nAll 7 Master Shared Links Tracker tasks set to Archived status\n\n## Client ClickUp tag deleted from workspace Settings → Tags\n\nLast updated: July 2026 | Owner: Revital Productions Account Manager\n\n"
